name: James Brown; The Godfather Of Soul 1970's
description:
This is a cool backstage photo of T.G.F.O.S. in the early 1970's  and that deep V makes me want to jump back and kiss myself, HIYYYA!

CLICK ON IMAGE TO ENLARGE

name: Tom Waits On Stage Early 1980's
description:
I found this packet of negatives at the flea market that only said 'TW Live.'
I took a chance and it turns out to be a rare early 80's live performance from one of the greats.


CLICK IMAGE TO ENLARGE

name: Woman By The Dashboard Light
description:
A beautiful young woman in the early 1960's is photographed by using only the overhead light in the car.

She has mysterious, Ann-Margret-Bye-Bye-Birdie starlet quality eyes and she is aware of it.  

Click Photo To Enlarge

name: Bing Crosby At A Parade
description:
Bing Crosby plays the role of parade Grand Master in a Texas parade in the 1950's


CLICK PHOTO TO ENLARGE

name: Riding In The Back Of Dad's Station Wagon
description:
Before the age of child safety seats and bicycle helmets, there was the 1960's. 

An age of smoking in cars with rolled up windows and piling kids in any space they could fit;  Including portions of the car usually reserved for luggage.

In this photo two kids make faces at passing cars in an attempt to have any contact with the outside world.

Click Photo To Enlarge

name: Ray Charles: 1970's
description:
Legendary musician Ray Charles plays the piano in the 1970's.
What I say?

CLICK IMAGE TO ENLARGE

name: Bikers Race In The Desert
description:
Motorcycle enthusiasts race their bikes in the desert ala The Wild Bunch

Even though the cars in the background are all pre 1940's, this picture is most likely taken after WWII when motorcycle culture exploded with soldiers coming home and looking for an adrenalin fix.  

Click On Photo To Enlarge

name: Mid 1970's pinball
description:
This is an exquisite example of what most people's experience at an arcade was in the mid 70's; watching some long haired teen shoot the lights out of a pinball game.

CLICK IMAGE TO ENLARGE

options.name: 8x10 Open Edition Black and White Print

name: Leonardo DiCaprio shirtless, smoking and in his teens
description:
Here is a very rare find.  This is a photo from some portrait shoot with a young Leo DiCaprio around the time he made the Basketball Diaries.  He was trying to kick his child star image so he is of course shirtless and smoking a cigarette. Our gain.
These will probably sell quickly.  Enjoy

CLICK PHOTO TO ENLARGE

name: Parade Float: 1963
description:
"Products On Parade"
Beauty queens adorn a float in a 1963 Wisconsin parade.
This is a beautifully kept slide from almost fifty years ago.

Click On Photo To Enlarge

name: Streets Of San Francisco: 1965
description:
An array of women on their way to work, wait for the light to change on a San Francisco street corner.

Click the photo or NEXT button to see a close up of the woman in the poodle skirt with one glove, a wedding ring and a broken finger.

Click Photo To Enlarge

name: California Oil Rigs 1950's Color Photo
description:
A photographer gets out of their car to take a dusk photo of some oil derricks in California. 

CLICK IMAGE TO ENLARGE

name: Young Country Singer 1950's
description:
A young country boy in the 1950's, with dreams of marrying into The Carter Family, shows off his guitar by the chicken coops.


Click Photo To Enlarge

name: Mickey Mantle Era Yankee At the Bat
description:
This is a beautiful slide of  a New York Yankee in the Mickey Mantle era. (Late 1950's to mid 1960's)

It was taken at the original Yankee Stadium.  It would make a great small print.

Click Photo To Enlarge

name: Couple Walking In New York City: 1960's
description:
A fashionable New York City couple walk hand in hand down the street. 

This photo was shot in the style of street photography master Garry Winogrand.  

Click Photo To Enlarge  (Bonus: click 'NEXT" to see this image framed)

name: Sprint Car Race: 1930's or 40's
description:
A great action shot of a sprint car racing around a dirt track.  The scratches and nicks are part of the charm of this old image.

CLICK IMAGE TO ENLARGE

name: Wu Tang Clan from 1994
description:
This is one negative from a whole shoot that I found with The Wu Tang Clan from 1994.  All your favorites are here: Ghost Face, Method Man, Reakwon and of course Ol' Dirty Bastard.

I have found other images of this same photo shoot online and I think it may have been done for their label.  This is the most contemporary negative that Negative Collection is offering.

CLICK IMAGE TO ENLARGE

name: View Of The Brooklyn Bridge 1930's
description:
A beautiful panoramic negative of New York City's Brooklyn Bridge in the 1930's.
The grain and the haziness of the afternoon that is was shot on gives this image a Stieglitz-esq feel.  So little has change and so much has changed  since this image was first taken.

CLICK IMAGE TO ENLARGE

name: Hockey Players Wife On The Side Lines
description:
The wife of a Montreal Canadiens Hockey Player checks the scoreboard.
Notice her C.H. neck brooch.  A classic


CLICK IMAGE TO ENLARGE

name: Cubs In First Place: 1947
description:
Cub's legend Phil Cavarretta slides hard on a stolen base attempt at Wrigley Field during the 1947 season.
This is not the last time the Cubs were in first place, but it sure does feel that way sometimes.

For a bonus click the NEXT arrow to see the actual newspaper clipping of this photo that I found with the negative.

name: Louis Armstrong Sings In A Night Club
description:
An intimate photograph of legendary singer Louis Armstrong singing in a small night club.

Click Photo To Enlarge

name: Mother And Daughter In Manhattan early 1960's
description:
A mother and daughter walk past New York's famous bookstore Scribner's in the early 1960's.

They walk in lockstep and while the mother holds a protective grip to her young daughters hand. The relationship brings Mad Men's Betty and Sally Draper to mind

CLICK IMAGE TO ENLARGE

name: Fireman takes a smoke break: 1960's
description:
The exhaustion on this firefighter's face tells you about the night he has had.  
This is a rare night time photograph taken with existing light without a flash.  This lends me believe that this may have been a professional photographer on assignment.

Click Photo To Enlarge
(Bonus: Click NEXT for tighter detail shot)

name: Couple From The 1970's
description:
This exquisite moment captures exactly what I remember the 1970's looking like.  Every meaty-pawed guy had a woman that was way out of their league and the sun was in a constant state of setting.

This image comes right out of the William Eggleston play book; Southern, 70's, perfect light and perfect moment.

This could be the finest image that we have on the site.

CLICK IMAGE TO ENLARGE

name: Cowgirl Practices Lasso Routine
description:
A rodeo cowgirl practices her lasso routine behind the tent before she goes on.  

Click On Photo To Enlarge

name: Violinist's Work Space: Glass Plate Negative
description:
A very quite photograph of the practice space of a violinist.  This is probably shot in the very early 1900's.
This comes from a small glass plate negative

CLICK IMAGE TO ENLARGE

name: Spying Through A Telescope: 1938
description:
This is a fascinating diptych taken trough a telescope from an apartment window.  This particular photographer had a keen interest in viewing women from a distance. 

The paper bag that the negatives came in is from Seattle and is marked '1938' in pencil as well as a creepy personal note to 'get your scrapbook.'

As a bonus, click 'NEXT IMAGE' for a detail shot and a shot of the paper bag.

name: Drag Ball San Francisco
description:
A beautiful drag queen makes a fabulous entrance dressed as Carmen Miranda to a drag ball in San Francisco.

You go gurrrl.

Click Photo To Enlarge  (Bonus: click 'NEXT" to see this image framed)

name: Soap Box Race
description:
Neighborhood kids ready themselves for an old fashioned, downhill soap box race.

Since the image is from the early 60's, there is some ware on it in the shape of yellow specks in the corner but that only adds to the etherial, memory style quality of the photo.

Click On Photo To Enlarge

name: Steam Engine Train: Boston & Maine
description:
A perfectly exposed negative of a coal burning train.  This is a large negative that will produce a crystal clear print in either 11x14 or 16x20 inch sizes.  

A must have for any train enthusiast.

Click Photo To Enlarge

name: Chicago Race Riots: 1968
description:
Civil unrest broke out upon the announcement of the assassination of Dr. Martin Luther King on April 4th, 1968.  
Lyndon Johnson called sent 5000 National Guardsmen in with 'shoot to kill' orders for arsonists and 'shoot to maim' orders for looters.

Some stores with the spray painted words 'Soul Brother' were passed over by looters and arsonists who mostly destroyed their own West Side neighborhood.

Click Photo To Enlarge

name: Pop Warner Football: Early 60's
description:
A young quarterback runs the option play in hopes of achieving childhood memory-glory that he still talks about today.

This 4x5 negative makes a beautiful 16x20 print.

Bonus: Click NEXT to see a tighter detail of this image

name: Colt 1903 Pocket Hammerless On Display Case
description:
This is from a crystal clear 4x5 negative of a Colt 1903 Pocket Hammerless placed on a display case and then photographed.

This is the same gun Humphrey Bogart used in Casa Blanca.

Click On Photo To Enlarge

name: Early Flight: From Glass Plate Negative
description:
This is a photograph from the very early days of flight.  Based on the design of the plane I would say that it was shot between 1907-1910.
Possibly a Wright Model B.

I have included a detail shot of the plane if you scroll through.

CLICK IMAGE TO ENLARGE

name: Chicago Street Meeting
description:
An amateur photographer catches an impromptu meeting on the streets of Chicago in the 1960's

Click Photo To Enlarge

name: Rodeo Clown Early 1960's
description:
A rare glimpse at a rodeo clown on his way to work.

This is the type of crispness and color that could only have been created by Kodachrome.


Click On Image To Enlarge

name: Early Days Of Drive Thru Dining
description:
The cropped out head in this image only leaves our imagination to ponder the delight this man is feeling to not have to get out of his car to eat a hamburger any longer.  

The driver's side window is rolled up, but the smaller window is cracked ever so slightly creating a perfect frame for the outside viewer as well as taunting him with that 1950's hamburger aroma.

Click Image To Enlarge

name: Sailors Headed to Guantanamo
description:
Sailors disembark from boats and board a train that says 'Guantanamo Y Occidente'

Click Photo To Enlarge
